gomodel:SYNGO_2982  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: From the Results section:\n\n\"We further characterized the proteins contained in the immunoisolated active zone by western blot analysis following 2-dimensional BAC/SDS-PAGE.\" (...) \"Other proteins identified included (...) and the ion channel VDAC1.\"\n\n\"Proteins of the presynaptic active zone were separated by SDS-PAGE and 1 mm gel slices were trypsinized and subjected to nanoLC ESI MS/MS.\" (...) \"Combining the nanoLC ESI MS/MS data with those obtained by western blotting and MALDI-TOF-MS (Table S2) we identified a total of 240 different proteins (Table 1).\"\n\n27/3/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: From M&M section:\n\"Three- to four-weeks-old male Wistar-rats weighing 150-225 g were obtained from Harlan-Winkelmann (Borchen, Germany) or from in house breeding.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-27" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2982" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

